I've posted to Empornium and PureTnA.  They
have higher standards.  I get alot of stuff
from Edonkey and try to post whatever is not
on the site/s at the time.  Screencaps/boxcovers,
help get more seeds, thus a longer torrent.  As
for comments, the stats can only tell you so much
about the success of a torrent.  I never know
whether they are accurate or not, anyway.
Comments can be help or hurtful, but for the
most part, can encourage the person to upload more
torrents.  If you give as much information as possible
about the torrent, there should be nothing to complain
about.  I like to have a successfull torrent!!!
